{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0652c1cb413a57e6be4e815d95932a3d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"From `src/clusterConsult.ts:63-80`:\n\n```ts\nconst staleFiles = findStaleFiles(cwd, loaded.fileHashes);\nif (staleFiles.length > 0) {\n  db.markClusterFactsheetStale(loaded.factsheet.id);\n  db.logClusterEvent({\n    clusterId: input.clusterId,\n    projectId: input.projectId,\n    eventType: \"cluster_refresh_required\",\n    details: {\n      factsheet_id: loaded.factsheet.id,\n      factsheet_version: loaded.factsheet.version,\n      changed_files: staleFiles\n    }\n  });\n  return errorPayload(ERROR_CODES.CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE, SPEC_ERROR_MESSAGES[ERROR_CODES.CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE], {\n    cluster_id: input.clusterId,\n    details: { changed_files: staleFiles }\n  });\n}\n```\n\nThree things happen atomically:\n\n1. **`db.markClusterFactsheetStale()`** — marks the factsheet record as `stale` and sets the cluster's `trust_state` to `untrusted` (`src/db.ts:746-758`).\n2. **`cluster_refresh_required` event logged** — records the stale files and factsheet version for observability.\n3. **Error returned** — `CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE` error with the list of changed files. The consult does **not** proceed.\n\nThe stale check is done by re-hashing every file in `cluster_file_hashes` against the stored hash/size (`src/clusterConsult.ts:199-215`). Only files scoped in the factsheet trigger invalidation — unrelated repo changes are ignored."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":187,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3694,"cache_read_input_tokens":89546},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e168c3-f7d3-48fb-8e86-0c3c3b4ba74a","uuid":"b904adc0-b063-437b-96c0-06c9df81e7c0"}
